==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek ''Herakles'' meaning "glory of Hera", from [[Hera]] + ''kles'', (glory).

===Proper noun===
'''Heracles'''
{{wikipedia}}
#{{greekmyth}}: Son of Zeus and Alcmene, a celebrated hero who possessed exceptional strength.  Most famous for his 12 labors performed to obtain immortality.

